      "content": """# Professional Post-Processing Workflow

## Efficient Professional Editing

A systematic workflow ensures consistent quality, saves time, and maintains organization for professional photography work.

### The Professional Workflow

**5-Stage Process:**
1. Import and Backup
2. Cull and Select
3. Batch Adjustments
4. Individual Refinements
5. Export and Delivery

### Stage 1: Import and Backup

**Import Strategy:**
• Create folder structure (Date_Client_EventType)
• Import to working drive
• Immediate backup to second location
• Cloud backup for critical projects

**Metadata:**
• Add copyright information
• Keywords for searchability
• Client/project tags
• Location data if relevant

**File Management:**
• Keep original RAW files
• Version control system
• Clear naming conventions
• Archive completed projects

### Stage 2: Culling and Selection

**First Pass (Reject Obvious):**
• Delete technical failures (focus, exposure)
• Remove duplicates
• Eliminate blinks, bad expressions
• Keep only potentially usable images

**Second Pass (Stars/Flags):**
• 1 star: Acceptable
• 2 stars: Good
• 3 stars: Client delivery
• 4 stars: Portfolio quality
• 5 stars: Competition/gallery

**Selection Efficiency:**
• Use keyboard shortcuts
• Quick decision-making
• Trust your first instinct
• Keep selection tight (5-10% typical)

### Stage 3: Batch Adjustments

**Global Corrections:**
• White balance
• Exposure baseline
• Lens corrections
• Noise reduction
• Sharpening

**Preset Application:**
• Develop style presets
• Apply to similar images
• Adjust as needed
• Maintain consistency

**Synchronization:**
• Sync settings across similar shots
• Same location/lighting batch together
• Adjust individual outliers
• Efficient time-saver

### Stage 4: Individual Refinements

**Targeted Adjustments:**
• Graduated filters (sky enhancement)
• Radial filters (vignettes, subject emphasis)
• Adjustment brush (dodging and burning)
• Color grading for mood

**Photoshop Integration:**
• Advanced retouching
• Compositing needs
• Precision masking
• Special effects

**Quality Control:**
• Zoom to 100% check sharpness
• Verify color accuracy
• Check for artifacts
• Consistency across set

### Stage 5: Export and Delivery

**Export Settings:**

**For Web/Social:**
• JPEG quality 70-80%
• sRGB color space
• 1920px or 2048px long edge
• Sharpen for screen

**For Print:**
• Maximum quality (90-100%)
• Adobe RGB or ProPhoto RGB
• Full resolution
• Sharpen for print medium

**For Clients:**
• Resolution per contract
• Watermark if needed
• Organized folder structure
• Upload to client gallery

