• Lead the eye into the scene
• Create depth (near-far relationship)
• Get low and close

**Visual Flow:**
• Leading lines (rivers, paths, rocks)
• S-curves
• Layering elements
• Balance and negative space

### Technical Precision

**Hyperfocal Distance:**
• Maximizing depth of field
• Focus point for front-to-back sharpness
• Use apps or charts
• Double the distance of the nearest object

**Tripod Discipline:**
• Essential for sharpness
• Disable IS/VR
• Use remote release or timer
• Weigh down in wind

### Mastering Filters

**Circular Polarizer (CPL):**
• Cuts glare and reflections
• Deepens blue skies
• Enhances foliage saturation
• Must be 90° to sun for max effect

**Neutral Density (ND):**
• Extends shutter speed
• Smooths water and clouds
• 3-stop, 6-stop, 10-stop usage
• Calculate exposure carefully

**Graduated ND (GND):**
• Balances bright sky and dark foreground
• Soft vs. Hard edge
• Reverse grad for sunsets

### Planning and Light

**Scouting:**
• Use apps (PhotoPills, TPE)
• Check sun/moon position
• Monitor weather patterns
• Arrive early, stay late

**The Light Phases:**
• Blue Hour (Pre-dawn/Post-sunset)
• Golden Hour (Sunrise/Sunset)
• Harsh Midday (Black & White potential)

Capture the grandeur of nature with intention and technical excellence.""",
