      "content": """# Street Photography

## The Decisive Moment

Street photography is about documenting life as it happens. It requires observation, anticipation, and quick reflexes.

### Overcoming Fear

**The Mindset:**
• You are an observer, not an intruder
• Most people don't care or notice
• A smile goes a long way
• Know your rights (public space laws)

**Strategies:**
• The "Tourist" act
• Shooting from the hip
• Waiting for the subject to enter the frame
• Fishing technique

### Technical Approaches

**Zone Focusing:**
• Pre-focus at a specific distance (e.g., 2-3 meters)
• Use small aperture (f/8 - f/11) for depth
• Bypass autofocus lag
• Instant shutter response

**Settings for Speed:**
• Shutter priority or Manual
• Min shutter 1/250s (freeze motion)
• Auto ISO is your friend
• Burst mode for fleeting moments

### Composition on the Fly

**Juxtaposition:**
• Contrasting elements (old/new, happy/sad)
• Humor and irony
• Color matching
• Geometry and shadows

**Layering:**
• Foreground, midground, background action
• Adds complexity and story
• Fill the frame
• Look for "frames within frames"

### Ethics and Respect

• Respect personal space
• Be sensitive to vulnerable subjects
• Delete if asked (usually best policy)
• Capture dignity, not mockery

Street photography is the ultimate practice in seeing and reacting.""",
