      "subtitle": "Creating emotional impact with color",
      "description": "Move beyond color correction to creative color grading. Learn color theory, split toning, and how to create a cohesive look for your portfolio.",
      "content": """# Color Grading Mastery

## Color is Emotion

Color correction is about accuracy; color grading is about feeling. Master the art of manipulating color to tell a story.

### Color Theory Basics

**Harmonies:**
• **Complementary:** Opposite colors (Teal/Orange) - High contrast, dynamic
• **Analogous:** Adjacent colors (Blue/Teal/Green) - Calming, harmonious
• **Monochromatic:** Single hue variations - Moody, unified
• **Triadic:** Three equidistant colors - Vibrant, balanced

**Psychology:**
• **Warm (Red/Orange/Yellow):** Energy, passion, nostalgia, danger
• **Cool (Blue/Teal/Purple):** Calm, sadness, mystery, cold
• **Green:** Nature, sickness, envy

### Tools of the Trade

**Curves:**
• The most powerful tool
• Adjust individual R, G, B channels
• Create S-curves for contrast
• Lift blacks for "matte" look

**Split Toning (Color Grading Panel):**
• Shadows: Cool tones (Blues/Teals)
• Highlights: Warm tones (Oranges/Yellows)
• Midtones: Balance the transition
• The "Cinematic Look" secret

**HSL/Mixer:**
• Hue: Shift colors (e.g., green foliage to autumn orange)
• Saturation: Intensity control
• Luminance: Brightness of specific colors

### Creating a Style

**Consistency is Key:**
• Develop presets for your look
