      "description": "Learn professional retouching workflows including Frequency Separation and Dodge & Burn. Achieve flawless results that retain skin texture.",
      "content": """# Professional Retouching

## The Art of Invisible Editing

Professional retouching improves the image without making it look "photoshopped." Texture is sacred.

### The Workflow

1. **RAW Processing:** Correct exposure/WB first
2. **Healing/Cleaning:** Remove temporary blemishes (pimples, stray hairs)
3. **Dodge & Burn (Macro):** Shape the face/body
4. **Dodge & Burn (Micro):** Smooth skin transitions
5. **Frequency Separation:** Fix color/texture independently
6. **Color Grading:** Final look
7. **Sharpening:** Output specific

### Frequency Separation (FS)

**Concept:**
Separates the image into two layers:
• **Low Frequency (Color/Tone):** Blurs, shadows, highlights
• **High Frequency (Texture):** Pores, hairs, fine lines

**Why use it?**
• Fix blotchy skin tone without losing pore texture
• Remove texture bumps without changing skin color
• The industry standard for beauty work

### Dodge & Burn (D&B)

**Concept:**
Lightening (Dodge) and Darkening (Burn) specific areas to shape light and smooth transitions.

**Technique:**
• Use 50% Grey layer in Overlay/Soft Light mode
• Paint with white (dodge) or black (burn) at low flow (1-3%)
• **Micro D&B:** Even out skin patches frame by frame
• **Macro D&B:** Contour cheekbones, nose, forehead

### What to Keep vs. Remove

**Remove:**
• Temporary blemishes (acne, cuts)
• Distracting stray hairs
• Redness/veins in eyes (reduce, don't remove completely)

**Keep (or reduce opacity):**
• Permanent features (moles, scars - ask client)
• Expression lines (smile lines)
• Skin texture (NEVER blur skin completely)

Retouching is digital makeup. Less is often more.""",
