      "content": """# Advanced Photoshop

## Limitless Creativity

Photoshop allows you to create what the camera cannot capture. Mastering layers and masks is the key.

### Luminosity Masks

**What are they?**
Selections based on brightness values.
• "Lights" selection (highlights only)
• "Darks" selection (shadows only)
• "Midtones" selection

**Uses:**
• Targeted contrast adjustments
• Blending multiple exposures (manual HDR)
• Protecting highlights while lifting shadows
• More precise than global sliders

### Compositing Basics

**Matching Elements:**
For a composite to look real, you must match:
1. **Perspective:** Horizon lines must align
2. **Lighting:** Direction, quality (hard/soft), and color
3. **Resolution/Noise:** Grain structure must match
4. **Focus:** Depth of field consistency

**Selection Tools:**
• Pen Tool (most precise)
• Select Subject / Sky (AI powered)
• Refine Edge / Select and Mask (for hair/fur)

### Advanced Blending Modes

• **Multiply:** Darkens (keeps darks, drops whites) - Good for shadows
• **Screen:** Lightens (keeps whites, drops blacks) - Good for overlays/flares
• **Overlay/Soft Light:** Contrast (darkens darks, lightens lights) - Good for texture
• **Color:** Applies hue/saturation only - Good for recoloring

### Content-Aware Tools

• **Content-Aware Fill:** Remove large objects
• **Content-Aware Move:** Reposition objects
• **Content-Aware Scale:** Resize background without distorting subject

Photoshop is a toolset. Don't let the tools dictate the art; let your vision guide the tools.""",
